      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SIR TICK (1) was out of the placings last time when fifth at The Gardens (30.25) but scored four back at Maitland (22.57). Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Has ability and is a key runner. EL REY (8) is a promising type who notched his 8th career success when too good (29.72) at this track last time. Hard to go past form here at this journey. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Can make it back-to-back wins. JUNIPER ROSE (2) will take beating coming off a useful 29.79 victory at Q Parklands over 520m. Top win latest and rates a key player again. NOVA REIGN (7) scored by one length last time (29.97) in a Grade 5 over 515m at this track. Already a winner from this draw.",
